=== Running a single-machine setup ===


Run simulation.Boot.java as a Java application.

The scenario and other settings are placed in simulation.BootSettings.java

Useful scenarios are the ones in scenarios/examples




=== Running a distributed setup (using 2 PCs) ===

Example: running scenario/phase2 on 2 machines - MachineA (with main container, IP-A, port-A) and MachineB (IP-B, port-B):
(Commands ran from the project's root directory)

MachineA:
* Windows:
 java -cp bin:lib/log4j-1.2.16.jar:lib/jade.jar simulation.Boot scenario/phase2/scenarioAdministration-distributed.xml null -1 IP-A port-A

* Linux:
 java -cp bin;lib/log4j-1.2.16.jar;lib/jade.jar simulation.Boot scenario/phase2/scenarioAdministration-distributed.xml null -1 IP-A port-A



MachineB:
* Windows:
 java -cp bin:lib/log4j-1.2.16.jar:lib/jade.jar simulation.Boot scenario/phase2/scenarioRoom-distributed.xml IP-A port-A IP-B port-B

* Linux
 java -cp bin;lib/log4j-1.2.16.jar;lib/jade.jar simulation.Boot scenario/phase2/scenarioRoom-distributed.xml IP-A port-A IP-B port-B
 




=== Running / testing the Android Client ===

Using the emulator:
* Prerequisites
** get the SDK Starter Package [[http://developer.android.com/sdk/index.html]]
*** get the Android SDK 2.3.3 (SDK Platform package) \\ (general page [[http://developer.android.com/sdk/android-2.3.3.html]])
*** [optional - if starting a device cannot load .ini] set ANDROID_SDK_HOME to the location of the .android folder. 
*** use the AVD manager to create a new device. 
** Install ADT plugin for Eclipse: update site: [[https://dl-ssl.google.com/android/eclipse/]] \\
(general page: http://developer.android.com/sdk/eclipse-adt.html)
** Put the path to adb.exe in PATH (e.g. C:\Program Files\Android\android-sdk\platform-tools)

* Running
** (clear Android console and logcat contents)
** launch the virtual device (using AVD manager)
** run tATAmI-Android/run.bat
** run Boot as Java Application (no arguments)
** run tATAmI-Android as Android Application
***  Host: IP of the main platform in the local network -> Use
** 'Create agents' 
** monitoring: use Console/DDMS and LogCat view, adding a filter for Application Name: "org." (or waiting for an autogenerated filter to show up)

